<page_title>Diffusion of gas molecules</page_title>
<text>Diffusion of gas molecules

Imagine there is a source of perfume in a room. If you are outside the room and the door is open, you will smell it. This is because the perfume molecules can diffuse in the air. The follow model illustrates this.

 
   

There are two subsets of molecules, marked by different colors. These molecules are identical except for their colors. The big rectangle in the middle of the room and the four smaller ones represent some sort of furniture inside the room. Like the brick walls, they stay on the &quot;stage&quot; to provide objects with which the molecules will collide with in their movement.

  

